  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clean Fuels and Cookstoves for Schools in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A Ugandan school district is in dire need of better wood-burning stoves and sustainable fuels for cooking.  Our program will train students to make fuel briquettes from agricultural waste. Our improved cookstoves will reduce fuel consumption and hazardous smoke.  Once established, the program will expand to the surrounding communities to meet their fuel needs and improve public health.  Sustainable tree farming will be encouraged to provide additional fuel/income sources. Jobs will be created.</narrative>
  </description>
